  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense. It involves taking money obtained through illegal activities (like drug trafficking or fraud) and making it appear to have come from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal money into the financial system\n2. Layering - concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration - making the money appear legal and usable\n\nIt's illegal in most countries and can result in significant legal penalties, including:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n\nThe specific laws and penalties vary by jurisdiction, but it's generally considered a serious financial crime.",
